In this Python script, we will generate Rust code that implements a bubble sort algorithm, specifically tailored for performance optimization on small arrays of integers. This serves as an introduction to how Rust can handle array sorting efficiently.

SECTION 2: Python Script Setup

```python
# Python script starts here
def generate_rust_bubble_sort():
    rust_code = '''
    fn bubble_sort(arr: &mut [i32]) {
        let mut n = arr.len();
        let mut swapped = true;
        while swapped {
            swapped = false;
            for i in 1..n {
                if arr[i - 1] > arr[i] {
                    arr.swap(i - 1, i);
                    swapped = true;
                }
            }
            n -= 1;
        }
    }
    '''
